║  HELIX TRAINER — Exercise 9.1: Pickers                          ║
║  Category: Space Mode            Difficulty: ★★★ Advanced       ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

COMMANDS TO LEARN
─────────────────
  Space f   File finder (fuzzy search)
  Space F   File finder (from current directory)
  Space b   Buffer picker (open files)
  Space g   Changed files picker (git modified)
  Space j   Jumplist picker
  Space '   Reopen last picker

MNEMONIC: Space = leader, f=file, b=buffer, g=git, j=jump

INSTRUCTIONS
────────────
  Space mode pickers are your primary navigation tools in Zed.
  This exercise is a reference card — fill in the correct command
  for each navigation scenario.

  Practice these in your real workflow after completing this exercise.

────────────────────────── PRACTICE ──────────────────────────────

NAVIGATION SCENARIO                              COMMAND
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Open any file in the project by name:            ???
Open any file starting from current dir:         ???
Switch between already-open files:               ???
See which files you've modified (git):           ???
Jump back to a previous location:                ???
Reopen the last picker you used:                 ???

────────────────────────── EXPECTED ──────────────────────────────

NAVIGATION SCENARIO                              COMMAND
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Open any file in the project by name:            Space f
Open any file starting from current dir:         Space F
Switch between already-open files:               Space b
See which files you've modified (git):           Space g
Jump back to a previous location:                Space j
Reopen the last picker you used:                 Space '

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
HINTS (read only if stuck):
  Hint 1: Space f is the most-used command — fuzzy file finder.
  Hint 2: Space b shows a list of currently open buffers.
  Hint 3: Space g shows git-modified files — great for reviews.
